    <h1>🏋️ Gym Management Web App</h1>

    <p>Welcome to the <strong>Gym Management Web App</strong>! This web application helps gym administrators manage members, schedules, payments, and more, with a sleek and user-friendly interface.</p>

    <h2>🌟 Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Member Registration &amp; Management</strong>: Track members, their subscription plans, and personal details.</li>
        <li><strong>Admin Panel</strong>: Manage the entire gym ecosystem with a central admin dashboard.</li>
        <li><strong>Supplements</strong>: Manage the supplements available.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>🛠️ Tech Stack</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Frontend</strong>: HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript</li>
        <li><strong>Backend</strong>: Node.js, Express.js</li>
        <li><strong>Database</strong>: MySQL</li>
        <li><strong>Tools &amp; Libraries</strong>:
            <ul>
                <li><code>bcrypt.js</code> for password encryption</li>
                <li><code>nodemailer</code> for sending emails</li>
                <li><code>sequelize</code> ORM for database operations</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>🚀 Installation</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Clone the repository:
            <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/asta-maxx/gym-management.git</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>Install the dependencies:
            <pre><code>cd gym-management
npm install</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>Set up the MySQL database:
            <ul>
                <li>Create a new MySQL database.</li>
                <li>Import the SQL schema (using the provided <code>/gym.sql</code> file).</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Configure environment variables:
            <ul>
                <li>Create a <code>.env</code> file in the root directory.</li>
                <li>Add the following environment variables:
                    <pre><code>DB_HOST=your_database_host
DB_USER=your_database_username
DB_PASSWORD=your_database_password
DB_NAME=your_database_name
PORT=4000</code></pre>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Start the app:
            <pre><code>npm start</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>Open your browser and visit: <code>http://localhost:4000</code></li>
    </ol>

    <h2>📂 Folder Structure</h2>
    <pre><code>├── public              # Static files (HTML, JS, images)
   ├── styles          # CSS
   ├── routes              # Application routes
   └── server.js           # Main entry point of the application</code></pre>

    <h2>👩‍💻 Usage</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Admin</strong> can:
            <ul>
                <li>Register new members.</li>
                <li>Add Supplements.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ul>

